Fredrik is sharing his thoughts on the founder exodus from Norway. We both needed to get out of a country that rapidly turned hostile towards startup founders.

1) what's going on in Norway
2) why i'm in switzerland

gruezi!

cast.text:
Norway Shrugged 🇳🇴🤷

My story recently racked up over 100 million views on this website.

As a startup founder in Norway I was facing an unrealized gains tax bill many times higher than my net income. No politician ever told me how I'm supposed to pay the bill, but I got put up on the Socialist Left party's "Wall of Shame" for speaking up.

With 100 of the top 400 tax payers leaving in just a couple of years present day Norway has chilling similarities to Ayn Rands 1957 dystopia "Atlas Shrugged".

I've written a post about why my motherland, one of the richest countries in the world, is facing an entrepreneurial exodus, how we got here and what the future might hold.

https://paragraph.xyz/@hagaetc/norway-shrugged

html.ogDescription: Recently, my story as a Norwegian entrepreneur facing an unrealized gains wealth tax bill many times higher than my net income went viral, amassing over 100 million views on X. A few years ago I publicly called out that this tax is both impossible-to-pay, but no politician would listen. So I made the difficult decision to leave my home country. I don’t know how I was supposed to pay the tax, but I recently found myself plastered on the "Wall of Shame" at the Socialist Left offices.

cast.text:
Would anyone like to build this frame for me? “Gift a Humankind Candle anonymously to a friend on Warpcast”

Ideally the flow looks like:
- purchaser writes the username of giftee in the frame 
- purchaser then is prompted to pay for a candle 
- creates an order in shopify (I can provide dev access) 
- ill manually reach out to the giftee for their address 
- Ill send them a candle 

It won’t be totally anonymous since I’ll be able to see the purchaser’s wallet but I won’t share it with the giftee. My preference is to OSS it. 

I’m bootstrapped so can’t pay much $$ for this, but will make you a custom candle or send you a candle of your choosing and provide a public testimonial.

show_title: GM Farcaster ep191 Friday December 6, 2024 with special guest @mats from dune
text:
This week I built https://hellobase.dev, where developers can say "Hello World" onchain for the first time. 

Specifically designed for developers who have never touched a blockchain, this app will walk them through the fundamentals of blockchain, Ethereum, and Base. It also will let devs deploy and interact with a simple greeting contract without ever leaving the page, thanks to Coinbase Smart Wallets 

If you're a Web3 developer and have Web2 peers, please feel free to share! The goal is to help developers understand the power of blockchain and make it accessible by speaking their language.

show_title: GM Farcaster ep191 Friday December 6, 2024 with special guest @mats from dune
text:
Update/reflections:

- 4 hours wasnt enough time but I was so annoyed I couldn’t get it working I kind of blocked out the rest of my life to keep cranking 
- needed to build a recursive function to climb thru conversation history so I could feed it back to the llm 
- finally got a happy path working and proved the bot can have a simple conversation, example:  https://warpcast.com/gmfc101/0xafd07b1d

- caveat: need to keep tagging the bot for it to reply, still need to figure out how to get it to answer if someone replies to it but doesn’t tag it 

- Claude cares a lot more about code quality than GPT. Claude wants me to harden code, gpt just wants me to push to prod 🤣 

So much more to do but we take it small step by small step. Still having fun. 

@kmacb.eth fyi

cast.text:
I have 4 uninterrupted hours of focus time today and I’m going to figure out how to give my @warpee.eth bot a memory so it can have a conversation with someone and not just reply to one-off casts.
